addLiquidity(address).details: Users should approve the tokens to this contract before calling this function.

params.recipient: The address that will receive the newly minted LP tokens.

recoverTokens(address,address).details: Can only be called by the owner. Tokens specified as thisToken or thatToken cannot be recovered.

params.recipient: The address of the recipient to receive the recovered tokens.
params.token: The address of the token to recover.

redeemLiquidity(address).details: Users should approve the LP tokens to this contract before calling this function.

params.recipient: The address that will receive the redeemed tokens.

returns.thatOut: The amount of thatToken the recipient will receive.
returns.thisOut: The amount of thisToken the recipient will receive.

skim(address,address).details: This function can be used to recover excess tokens of thisToken or thatToken sent to the contract.

params.recipient: The address that will receive the excess tokens.
params.token: The address of the token (thisToken or thatToken) to be transferred.

swap(address).details: This function is non-reentrant to prevent re-entrancy attacks.

params.recipient: The address to receive the swapped tokens.

swap(address,address).details: This function is non-reentrant to prevent re-entrancy attacks.

params.recipient: The address to receive the swapped tokens.
params.routingAgent: The address of the routingAgent contract.

addLiquidity(address).notice: Allows users to add liquidity to the pool. Taxed tokens are not supported.

recoverTokens(address,address).notice: Recovers tokens mistakenly sent to the Pool contract and sends them to the specified recipient.

redeemLiquidity(address).notice: Allows users to redeem their liquidity and receive the underlying tokens.

skim(address,address).notice: Allows the caller to transfer excess thisToken or thatToken to a specified recipient.

swap(address).notice: This function allows for swapping of tokens with the proceeds allocated to the development fund.

swap(address,address).notice: This function allows for swapping of tokens using a specified routingAgent.
